== Short Bio 
I am a doctoral candidate at Politecnico di Milano, working under supervision of prof. Lorenzo Fagiano and prof. Fredy Ruiz. I am particularly interested in data-driven optimization algorithms, with applications to UAVs and other aerospace systems. I earned a M.Sc. from RWTH Aachen, and have performed research in non-linear and multi-agent control for HVDC power systems. After my M.Sc. I have worked on a radio payload currently onboard the microsatellite Diwata-2.

== News 
- \[2022.05.08\] Experimental results using SMGO accepted for presentation at CCTA 2022: "Direct control design using a Set Membership-based black-box optimization approach".
- \[2022.05.07\] New paper is out!: "SMGO-Δ: Balancing Caution and Reward in Global Optimization with Black-Box Constraints" in /Information Sciences/, arXiv pre-print available [https://arxiv.org/abs/2202.11445 here], code [https://github.com/lorenzosabugjr/smgo-delta here]!
- \[2021.12.02\] Our paper "SMGO: A Set Membership Approach to Data-Driven Global Optimization" is [https://www.journals.elsevier.com/automatica/editors-choice/november-2021-automatica *Editors' Choice*] in /Automatica/, November 2021 issue! This means that the paper is now freely accessible from the publisher [https://doi.org/10.1016/j.automatica.2021.109890 here].
- \[2021.07.27\] Our new results on "Trading-off safety, exploration, and exploitation in learning-based optimization: a Set Membership approach" has been *accepted* for presentation at CDC 2021!
- \[2021.06.14\] Our contribution "SMGO: A Set Membership Approach to Data-Driven Global Optimization" has been *accepted* for publication in /Automatica/ (vol. 57, no. 12)! arXiv pre-print available [https://arxiv.org/abs/2011.03837 here], code [https://github.com/lorenzosabugjr/smgo here]!
- \[2020.07.16\] Our new paper "On the use of set membership theory for global optimization of black-box functions" has been *accepted* for CDC 2020!
- \[2019.08.31\] I have now left the microsatellite development team at UP Diliman to embark on a new and exciting Ph.D. journey at Politecnico! I thank all my mentors and colleagues from this dynamic research group, for a highly productive and impactful work.
- \[2019.08.19\] Our article on wavelet-based protection for HVDC grids is now [https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijepes.2019.105475 online]!
- \[2019.04.26\] We are now announcing Diwata-2 amateur radio as *ready* for worldwide use! Link to UP Media coverage [https://www.up.edu.ph/index.php/surviving-the-big-one-with-diwata-2s-amateur-radio-unit/ here].
- \[2018.10.31\] Diwata-2 is launched to space today! See [https://www.up.edu.ph/index.php/diwata-2-takes-flight/ UP Media coverage].
- \[2018.07.16\] Our article on multi-agent-based frequency control for HVDC grids is [https://doi.org/10.1049/iet-rpg.2018.5120 out].
- \[2018.03.01\] Published [https://doi.org/10.1109/TPWRD.2018.2811560 online] our article on predictive sliding mode control for HVDC grids.

